Ludis Megalensibus. These were the games celebrated April 4th-9th iu honour of the Magna (μεγάλη) Mater or Cybele, a Phrygian goddess whose worship was introduced into Rome 205 B.c.: Liv. 29. 10, 11. Theatrical representations did not form part ol the festival till 19413.c. The Trinummus was probably first performed about 188 rae. See 990 note. ·

Argumentum. Arguments in the form of acrostics, the first letters of the lines spelling the name of the play, were inserted, in the opinion of some authorities, during the revival of letters at Rome in the first century lac. They were, however, attributed bysome of the older editors to Priscian, who lived about the latter part ol the fifth century A.D., aud their Acrostic sorm seems to indicate a comparatively late origin.
